{"outcome":{"note":{}},"phase":"product","detail":"---\n\n### Summary for the next phase (architect\/plan)\n\nThe deliverable is a thin composition layer — ~15–20 lines of implementation. There is zero ambiguity about the semantics because every edge case (empty input, whitespace, maxLength guard, chunk invariants) is already handled by the existing functions and flows through naturally:\n\n- `normalizeText('')` \/ `normalizeText('   ')` → `\"\"` → `chunkText(\"\")` → `[]` → `[]`\n- `maxLength <= 0` → `chunkText` throws → `prepareForSynthesis` throws\n- Every chunk ≤ maxLength because `chunkText` guarantees it\n- Content is preserved because `chunkText` guarantees exact reconstruction via join\n\nThe implementation file goes at `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/prepare-for-synthesis.ts`, the test file at `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/prepare-for-synthesis.test.ts`. Both follow the existing conventions (vitest, `describe`\/`it`\/`expect`, ESM imports from sibling modules). No other files need to change.","at":804599045.500238,"id":"50-628","ticketId":"50"}
