{"ticketId":"50","at":804599249.428803,"id":"50-670","outcome":{"note":{}},"phase":"planning","detail":"thinking: ---\n\n## Concrete Facts for the Planner — Issue #50\n\n### 1. Project Structure & Stack\n\n| Fact | Detail |\n|---|---|\n| **Repo root** | Monorepo with npm workspaces: `apps\/*`, `packages\/*` |\n| **Target package** | `apps\/web` (`@vokda\/web`, SvelteKit + Vite) |\n| **Language** | TypeScript 5.4, strict mode, `moduleResolution: \"bundler\"` |\n| **Test runner** | vitest 4.x, config at `apps\/web\/vitest.config.ts` — glob pattern `src\/**\/*.test.ts`, jsdom environment |\n| **Key scripts** | `npm run test` (root) → `vitest run` in `apps\/web`; `npm run build:web` → `node scripts\/publish-catalog.mjs && npm run -w apps\/web build` |\n\n### 2. Existing Dependencies (all confirmed via file reads)\n\n| Symbol | Source file | Signature | Key behavior |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `chunkText` | `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/chunk-text.ts` | `(text: string, maxLength: number): string[]` | Trims input; returns `[]` for empty; throws on `maxLength <= 0`; guarantees each chunk `<= maxLength` and `chunks.join('') === trimmedOriginal` |\n| `normalizeText` | `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/text-utilities\/normalize-text.ts` | `(text: string): string` | Collapses all whitespace runs to single spaces, then trims; returns `\"\"` for empty\/whitespace-only |\n| `wordCount` | `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/text-utilities\/word-count.ts` | `(text: string): number` | Calls `normalizeText` internally; returns 0 for empty\/whitespace; splits on spaces and returns length |\n\n**Barrel**: `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/text-utilities\/index.ts` re-exports `normalizeText`, `wordCount`, and `truncateWords`.\n\n### 3. Key Semantic Interaction (critical for composition)\n\n`wordCount` **already calls `normalizeText` internally** (line 33 of `word-count.ts`). This means `wordCount` on a chunk that came from `normalizeText` → `chunkText` will double-normalize — but `normalizeText` is idempotent: normalizing already-normalized text is a no-op. No correctness issue.\n\n`chunkText` trims its input first. Since `normalizeText` already trims, the double-trim is a no-op.\n\nThe **reconstruction invariant** (`chunks.join('') === normalizedText`) is automatically satisfied by `chunkText`'s own guarantee — `chunkText`'s join invariant is relative to its *own* trimmed input, which after normalization is the already-normalized string.\n\n### 4. What Does NOT Exist Yet\n\n- No file at `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/prepare-for-synthesis.ts`\n- No file at `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/prepare-for-synthesis.test.ts`\n- No reference to `prepareForSynthesis` or `SynthesisChunk` anywhere in the codebase\n\n### 5. Test Conventions (from existing co-located tests)\n\n- **Import style**: `import { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest'`\n- **File location**: co-located alongside the source (e.g., `chunk-text.test.ts` next to `chunk-text.ts`)\n- **Header**: JSDoc block describing test coverage\n- **Structure**: top-level `describe('functionName', () => { ... })` wrapping individual `it(...)` cases\n- **No barrel\/export update needed** — the issue scope is the module + tests only\n\n### 6. Module Design (derived from acceptance criteria + dependency behaviors)\n\nThe new module `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/prepare-for-synthesis.ts` needs:\n\n```ts\nexport interface SynthesisChunk { text: string; wordCount: number; }\nexport function prepareForSynthesis(text: string, maxLength: number): SynthesisChunk[]\n```\n\n**Implementation logic** (all by delegation):\n1. Call `normalizeText(text)` → if result is `\"\"` (empty\/whitespace), return `[]`\n2. Call `chunkText(normalized, maxLength)` → `maxLength <= 0` throws via `chunkText`'s guard\n3. Map each chunk string to `{ text: chunk, wordCount: wordCount(chunk) }`\n4. Return the array\n\n**Note**: The empty\/whitespace check can be done either before calling `chunkText` (checking `normalizeText` output) or after (relying on `chunkText(\"\")` returning `[]`). Either works since `chunkText` returns `[]` for empty strings. The explicit check on normalized output is cleaner and avoids an unnecessary call.\n\n### 7. Verification\n\n- `npm run test` runs vitest — the new test file at `src\/**\/*.test.ts` will be auto-discovered\n- `npm run build:web` runs the SvelteKit build (via `vite build` after catalog publishing) — the new module has no UI dependencies, so no special build concerns"}
